https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43772362/how-to-print-a-specific-row-of-a-pandas-dataframe

1. Using index to slicing dataframe by row or by column

1) df.loc[row,column]  
   
    ==> df.loc[0,:] ## Return 1st row, all columns
    
    ==> df.loc[0,'column_name']  ## first row, specific columns
    
2) iloc    
  
  ==> df.iloc[0,0:3]  ==> For first row and some specific column i.e first three cols
  
3) ix  

4)  df[df['domainName']=='Data Controls'].iloc[0]['domainID']
  ==> a. Filter rows with column domainName =='Data Controls'
         get value of column domainID of first row
         
         
         
         


